+## Additional Risks
+- The prompt does not define what should happen to `cancelConfirmType` if a red request resolves remotely or the user interacts with another tile first, so the confirm panel can become stale/orphaned.
+- Validation is strong on layout and happy-path send/undo flows, but it does not require testing network failure, retry, or legacy `menu` records even though those are the highest-risk behavior changes.
